The Acreage

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

"Where is Satan not? Tell me.
I would invent him if he did not exist,
and he would emerge, one evening from my silence."

Sabbat
Hélèn Picard

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

PRESS ANY KEY

HOW TO PLAY:

MOVE AROUND THE WORLD by entering abbreviated compass points
(Enter 'W' to go west or 'SE' to go southeast)

EXAMINE ANY OBJECT in capital letters with 'Look'
(Enter 'look at lamp' or 'x lamp' to examine a LAMP or switch it on.)

PICK UP AND INTERACT WTIH OBJECTS in capital letters with 'Take'
(Enter 'take book' to pick up a BOOK, do not use 'take all')

VIEW YOUR INVENTORY by entering 'i'

INTERACT WITH NPCS with 'Talk'
(Enter 'talk to clerk' to ask THE CLERK questions or buy items)

SEE AVAILABLE EXITS by entering 'look'

Enter 'map' to pull up a map of the places you've been

Enter 'save' to save your game

*   Enter 'tips' to see this message again

The writer and game designer can be reached at dctozier@gmail.com

PRESS ANY KEY TO BEGIN

PART ONE: OLD BEGINNINGS

Desmond's whistling falls through the yultide bells ringing in your dreams before prevailing and leading you back into the waking world. It's cold here. A not entirely unpleasant blend of stale and freshly burnt tobacco waits for you. The last motel room was nearly identical in its delapidation, despite being located far across the acreage, somewhere in the Pisces constellation.

It was there that death sought you yet again, this time in the form of a Tremont security beamshot cannon. An indirect hit. Your ship, The Vigil, managed to escape through the fold, but it's not going to make another journey in its current condition. So you landed on Bluèl, the nearest populated planet.

It's been like this every step of the way. What was supposed to be a quick transport job continues to spiral out into something more. You should have called it quits long ago, but something is keeping you here.

He calls himself Isaac.

PRESS ANY KEY

Motel Room

You find yourself in a motel room defined by filth and monastic efficiency. A single brass flame LAMP illuminates the foulness of your situation with arrhythmic orange light. Mildewed blankets cover the twin BEDS, both of which are held together by overlapping strips of thick, red industrial tape.

The floor, walls, and ceiling are enduring entropy each in their own unique way. Water stains pool above you; beneath your feet several rugs hide multicolored stains in the green carpet. The wallpaper is failing at its edges, peeling away in large swatches to reveal the synthetic wood walls beneath.

There's a WINDOW, though it's so filthy you would be better off guessing about the world beyond.

PRESS ANY KEY

Familiar voices echo within the architecture of your being.

SYNAPSE: Based on the wallpaper pattern (cancerian art deco passé), the last time this motel saw renovations was the 2980s.

ANIMUS: Why would the manager bother with renovations? His customers tend to have more pursuants than options.

SYNAPSE: The door doesn't even lock properly.

ANIMUS: Which is why we barely slept last night.

A ship passes low overhead, the first of the morning, rattling the room like a tin can in the wind. ISAAC sleeps soundly in one of the beds, beneath a small bundle of blankets. His gray tunic hides his face, for which you are grateful. DESMOND sits in the corner, using his teeth to tear bandages from a spool. A cigarette burns in an ashtray at his elbow.

SINEW: Fracture of his fifth metacarpal. Likely from punching that Tremont peace officer during yesterday's urgent exit.

"You're finally up. I need you to give Isaac his treatment," DESMOND says, wrapping the bandage around his hand. "Can't work the syringe with my hand like this. It's in the bathroom. Then we can grab a repair kit for your ship and head to Surst."

Bathroom >>> WEST
Motel Lobby >>> EAST
> w

> w

Motel Bathroom

You enter the dark bathroom and turn the knob mounted on the wall. Gas hisses momentarily behind the white tiles before a flint clicks and ignites the small flame of a sconce to illuminate the cramped space.

The bathroom exceeds the motel room in its state of disrepair. A small rectangular MIRROR hangs above the sink. The bathtub is stained with what you hope is rust. The toilet was clearly usable at some point, judging from the contents, but the thought of making physical contact with it rises bile in your throat.

SINEW: The only reason we’re keeping last night’s dinner down is because it was so meager.

There is an empty VIAL in the sink. (Enter "look at vial" to examine it)

Isaac's treatment, held in a glass SYRINGE, sits on the sink.

(Enter "take syringe" to pick up the syringe and add it to your inventory. Enter "i" to see what you're carrying.)

