Motel Bathroom

You look at the SYRINGE and your stomach turns. DESMOND has been injecting ISAAC with the thick sludge every week or so. You haven't asked why. As you pick up the SYRINGE another ship passes overhead, twice the size of the first one if the turbulence is any indication. As you attempt to gain your footing, you find instead a slick unknown substance. Your shoulder collides with the tiled wall and the SYRINGE tumbles away from your palm, falling to the floor where it shatters.

 SINEW: Oops.

Desmond’s voice booms from the other room to break the deafening silence, "Was that the treatment?!"

The bathroom door slams open and DESMOND's eys fall to the shattered glass on the floor.

He turns around and walks back into the room without looking at you.

Motel Room >>> EAST
