> e

> e

 MOTEL LOBBY

Flame lamps illuminate the dark, empty motel lobby in a wash of unsteady orange. A puddle spreading out from the corner of the room's cement floor emerges from a pipe running the length of the wall and across the ceiling. The smell of dust and wet stone greets you. A POSTER hangs on the wall by the front door.

A desk has been shoved haphazardly in the corner of the room, but no one is sitting there this early in the morning. A striped gray CAT sleeps on a window sill behind the empty desk.

Civic Resource District >>> NORTH
Motel Room >>> WEST
> n

> n

 SOUTHERN LANE, CIVIC RESOURCE DISTRICT

You walk alone through the empty pre-dawn streets of Bluèl. Flame lamps line the pathways before you, dousing the walls and wet pavement with dancing light of burnt orange. Frigid winds swirl with the scent of wet stone and smoke. Above the MOTEL, smokestacks of varying heights gently parcel out clouds of white, a stark contrast against the black firmament.

You are surrounded by the windows and doors of buildings no more than three or four stories high. They are each built of different material, but all are painted some shade of blue or gray.

Occasional ships rise slowly above the skyline, lilting like icebergs before vanishing upward into sweeping black clouds.

A CLINIC and GROCERY STORE are nearby. A short flight of stairs leads to a PAWNSHOP. Between two buildings you see a small TENT, firelight flickers from within. A row of vendor STALLS bisects the street.

PRESS ANY KEY

SYNAPSE: This is the southern lane of Bluèl’s Civic Resource District. A sorry collective of shops designed to meet the most basic demands of factory employees. Nearly all of them closed at this hour. Many appear to have been closed for decades.

ANIMUS: There are no trees here, or plants. Not even a wayward weed.

You pull your coat around you, but the cold wind finds its way through regardless.

