ALLEYWAY

You find a gap between the buildings, barely wide enough to accommodate your frame. Your coat pulls blue paster off the wall as your slip through.

 The narrow space appears to be funneling all the wind of Bluèl into a singular contained roar. Holding your hands in front of your eyes, you can still see that it's cleaner than you would expect an alleyway to be. There are no newspaper pages or other trash particles waiting to be caught in the wind whipping through. A wall of brick, easily nine feet tall rises on one side where it meets a hill of dirt that continues its ascent.

A row of SHACKS have been constructed against the brick wall. You pass by them on your way to the backside of the abandoned clinic.

Bluèl’s Civic Resource District >>> NORTH WEST
Clinic Exam Room >>> SOUTH
> s

> s

 CLINIC EXAM ROOM

The hinges of the door creak as you enter the clinic. The building is small, consisting of only an exam room, where you stand now, and a lobby. The exam room has been converted into a living room complete with a SOFA and RECORD PLAYER. A BASS guitar is leaning up against the corner. The door that leads to the lobby is missing, replaced by a FLAG draped over the frame.

If you're going to find the essage that Desmond demands, it will be somewhere around here.

You spend some time digging through the shelves and cupboards, but find only torn packaging and empty boxes. Dust is clinging to the back of your throat, but you are empty handed.

