 You push the flag out of the way as you enter the lobby. It's clean and free of dust, with the notable exception of the filthy windows. Years of dust have been left uncleaned, blocking the view of any curious passerby.

SYNAPSE: Someone lives here.

ANIMUS: In secret.

 There are two empty SLEEPING BAGS in the corner of the room, side by side on a wide rubber mat. Several SKETCHES have been pinned to the wall using large construction nails.

 There is a metal CRATE next to the bed being used as an impromptu nightstand for several unlit candles and a large yellow rotary PHONE.

There's a blue BOOK amongst the clutter.

