Motel Room

 You find yourself in a motel room defined by filth and monastic efficiency. A single brass flame LAMP illuminates the foulness of your situation with arrhythmic orange light. Mildewed blankets cover the twin BEDS, both of which are held together by overlapping strips of thick, red industrial tape.

