________________________________________________________

DESMOND stands as you walk through the door.

"Finally," he says, taking the canister and a leather satchel into the bathroom. You sit and listen to him work.

The gray light of dawn emerges against the foggy window, as the people of Bluèl, tense to face another day, rise nevertheless. Throughout the city, flames ignite under kettles and pans. Showers burst forth with water as hot as a sun. Feet find boots, and hands, gloves.

ISAAC sits up and pulls his tunic away from his small face to reveal two mechanical lenses where his eyes should be, each one polished to a void. As has become your habit, you try not to look at his thin parchment-colored skin or the cables running from the back of his shorn head. He is either an ancient man or an extremely ill child. You never bothered to ask.

SINEW: It's difficult to tell if he's even human.

SYNAPSE: Technically speaking, he is.

ANIMUS: Was. He's something else now entirely.

PRESS ANY KEY

ISAAC speaks suddenly, his lips not moving. The voice comes electronicaly from beneath his tunic.

"You are a worthy light upon a dark path,
So I ask of one more thing.
Sleep, in chemical form, will be needed.
Trust in me
And your faith in my works,
Will be a crown upon your head."

You're about to respond in plain language, to remind him that this is nothing more than a contract job when DESMOND emerges with a new syringe of violet and quickly pierces ISAAC's skin. Fluid swirls in the syringe before vanishing into his flesh. ISAAC does not respond to the intrusion, his eyes remaininng on you.

"Alright," DESMOND says. "Let's go. We'll find a repair kit, get your ship in working order, and be in Surst by end of day. If you have any questions about your contract, just talk to me."

Bathroom >>> WEST
Motel Lobby >>> EAST
> e

> e

 MOTEL LOBBY

The MANAGER, a boulder of a man, sits in a small chair behind a small desk where a small yellow leger is open, lit by a flame lamp built into the desk. His pen floats across the pages like a figure skater. He is wearing an almost white collared shirt with a small blue pocket square sticking out.

SINEW: What a specimen he is. Absolutely strapping.

He stops to pet the gray striped CAT, now awake. You watch as he feeds the animal from his hand, although upon closer inspection the CAT's jaws seem to only open and close above an empty palm. A silver spray of sparks ignites at the corner of its jaw. He looks up at you and redirects his attention as you walk in.

"Hello, sirs," he says, "How's your stay?"

"We'll be checking out now," DESMOND says, as he places a few cash notes onto the table. The MANAGER consults his leger, dragging his large finger down the rows. Seemingly satisfied, he takes the cash and makes a note.

"Well, alright then," he says. "You enjoy the rest of your time here."

"Ready?," DESMOND says, turning to you. "Let's go find a repair kit and leave this place."

