 SOUTHERN LANE, CIVIC RESOURCE DISTRICT

 The sun has begun to rise, but a thick cover of gray clouds keeps most of its light from reaching the district's streets. The flame lamps lining the path still flicker with their dark orange flames. The MOTEL sits in the shadow of taller buildings and an array of smokestacks. The apartments making up the the highest stories of the district have poured their inhabitants out into the lane where they slosh and ebb between the shop exteriors.

You stand amongst the blue and gray buildings and smoke of various fires burning rich, damp wood. Above an unreadable network of wires and black pipes, hauler ships continue tracing their paths to and from the acreage above.

