Grocery Store Entrance

You make your way across the street toward a single story building, light blue with a cornucopia of food painted above the entrance.

The grocery store is now open. You can see flame lamps inside flickering above shelves of cans and colorful boxes. A long line has formed at its entrance, beneath a concrete arch. There's no point in waiting to enter and you fear that trying to cut would end in a public execution. In a corner are NEWSPAPERS that may have at one point been used as a bed.

There is a SIGN posted to the front door.

