NORTHERN LANE, CIVIC RESOURCE DISTRICT

The crowd begins to thin as you enter the northern end of the CR District. Here too are the flame lamps you've become accustomed to, burning in the cold wind. The tracks of a light rail STATION cut across the district's lane. Beyond the tracks you see a long paved road that leads to the port, where you ship is waiting. You can still hear the crowd inside the bar. The windows of an OFFICE building glow with bright clean light.

There is a PROTESTER on the street corner, yelling slogans to an uncaring river of workers. A few smokers are igniting near the entrance of the BAR. The light rail train stops to collect a crowd of workers, all in blue overalls, before charging towards a long day's work.
________________________________________________________
Through the windows of the OFFICE building, you see two indviduals arguing, one with serious intensity, the other with a massive smile.

ISAAC holds his tunic tightly around himself. DESMOND's  eyes float towards the bar.

"Maybe I'll grab a beer before take off," DESMOND says.

"Vices make the possible, impossible," ISAAC says. "And time is at my heels."

DESMOND appears dejected, but continues following you through the district.

