Bluèl & GasTechnin Acreage Port

It's only a 20 minute walk to your ship, but the frigid air seems to slow both time and molecules alike. Finally, you arrive at the port, passing through the enormous open concrete gates. Your face is numb and fingertips burn with cold.

 Overall clad workers scatter and regroup throughout the port's expansive space, jumping over cables and fuel lines. The smell of burning of exhaust and various gasses cling immediately to your throat. You see your ship, THE VIGIL, dwarfed by enormous tankercrafts parked on either side. The spotlights of arriving and departing ships sweep the port, illuminating the scene with white light and shifting shadows.

The Vigil >>> EAST
Northern Lane, CR District >>> SOUTH
> x ship

> x ship

THE VIGIL is a medium sized passenger craft painted olive green with accents and serial numbers in bright yellow. Long windows, several inches thick, run down the sides. From the ground, you can see into the cockpit pusling with various instrument lights.

It's an older model, but one built to last.

SYNAPSE: It's an A-Class machine, built by the Corvor corporation in 3022. The internal systems are well maintained and pirate software offers agility unmatched by most ships this size.

It's illegal and unsafe to have a fold engine on a craft this small, but it wasn't hard to find someone willing to do it off the record.

 PRESS ANY KEY

Even in the anemic light of dawn you can see your ship has taken far more damage than you initially thought. Desmond lets out a low series of curses. The alloy hull on the starboard side of THE VIGIL is marred with coal-colored impact sites of shredded metal.

Their first of the Tremont Peace Keepers' beamshot made contact, a shimmering pillar of violent white but by the time their cannons sent a second shot, THE VIGIL had vanished into folded space, the beams carrying on harmlessly into the acreage.

ANIMUS: This was a close call, even by our standards.

SYNAPSE: If they had expected a craft this small to have its own fold engine, they would have started with missiles.

 “Look what they did to your ship," DESMOND says, running his rough hands run over the damage as though reading something written in the warped metal.

 PRESS ANY KEY

ISAAC pushes his hood off onto his shoulders, gears behind his lenses whisper mechanically as he inspects the damage. He speaks:

“My words are never light,
Strike first when I call you to do so.
Meet the moment without hesitation."

SINEW: Who is he to tell us what to do?

SYNAPSE: The damage speaks for itself, doesn’t it? The inner hull is nearing its breaking point. A repair kit will not suffice.

“You’ll need to find an engineer for this,” DESMOND says.

The Vigil >>> EAST
Northern Lane, CR District >>> SOUTH
