The northern end of the CR District is home to more small shops lit by the flame lamps you've become accustomed to, burning in the cold wind. The tracks of a light rail STATION cut across the district's lane. Beyond the tracks you see a long paved road that leads to the port, where you ship is waiting. You can still hear the crowd inside the bar. The windows of an OFFICE building glow with bright clean light.

There is a PROTESTER on the street corner, yelling slogans to an uncaring river of workers. A few smokers are igniting near the entrance of the BAR, huddling around one of the flame lamps.
________________________________________________________
Through the windows of the OFFICE building, you see two indviduals arguing, one with serious intensity, the other with a massive smile.

ISAAC holds his tunic tightly around himself. DESMOND's  eyes float towards the bar.

"Well, it looks like I do have time for the beer. Find an engineer and get your ship fixed," DESMOND says, slipping away from the group and disappearing into the bar.

ISAAC shakes his head and turns to you.

"He can no longer call my side 'home'.
You have been strong,
Where weakness fails.
Bring poison to his poison,
And in his slumber we will fly."

SYNAPSE: He's asking you to drug Desmond's beer. The best place to find a suitable substance is the pawn shop. It's not going to be on a shelf, but that clerk might be willing to help.

