GasTechnin Offices

The POSTERs and LOGOs plastered across the well-lit office tell you that this is GasTechnin's main office for Bluèl. The space is bright and free of dust.  Unlike the other buildings, this space is lit with electric lightbulbs. Emerald green plants of plastic decorate each of the four corners. Were it not for the massive painted LOGO looming over the office, you might forget, for a moment, which planet you are on.
________________________________________________________
The company SECRETARY is speaking cheerfully to a very angry, but stunningly beautiful, individual. They tower over the secretary's desk in a long black coat.

"Shanti, it's immaterial," the SECRETARY says. "Food tokens can not just be handed out. They must be earned. Worked for."

"We do work! It is not enough," SHANTI spits back. "You must know this. Everyone knows this."

The SECRETARY types something into his terminal.

"It looks like you should receive a pay check and tokens tomorrow," a sympthetic look crosses his face before he reaches behind his desk and produces few tokens. "This should hold you over until then."

"These are drink tokens," SHANTI says, examining them. "...and only for beer."

PRESS ANY KEY

The SECRETARY notices you and smiles in your direction. SHANTI, takes the drink tokens and storms past you and out of the office.

“I am just so sorry about that, sir,” he says.

You follow his eyes to see SHANTI making a rude gesture through the front window before walking out of view.

“Our friend seems to be having a bad day.”

His smile turns to an exaggerated frown. “Anyways!," his smile bounces back to life "We don’t get many visitors here, but we welcome them all the same! So welcome to the Bluèl branch of GasTechnin Interconstellation Enterprises!”

ANIMUS: I…don’t like this man.

 SINEW: He seems well fed and cleaner than anyone else here though. Maybe we should rob him?

 SYNAPSE: I don’t care for him either, but let’s not attract attention.

SINEW: …

SYNAPSE: Don’t sulk. If you still feel like robbing him after we complete the contract, we’ll come back.

“How can I help you gentlemen?,” he chimes, his smile slipping as his gaze lands upon ISAAC.

