 MOTEL LOBBY

Flame lamps illuminate the dark, empty motel lobby in a wash of unsteady orange. A puddle spreading out from the corner of the room's cement floor emerges from a pipe running the length of the wall and across the ceiling. The smell of dust and wet stone greets you. A POSTER hangs on the wall by the front door.

The MANAGER, a boulder of a man, sits in a small chair behind a small desk where a small yellow leger is open. His pen floats across the pages like a figure skater. He is wearing an almost white collared shirt with a small blue pocket square sticking out.

A flame lamp built into the desk is lit, illuminating both him and a striped gray CAT sitting upright on the counter. He is still pretending to feed the CAT from his empty hand. A silver spray of sparks ignites at the corner of the animal's jaw.

ISAAC stands in the lobby looking at the cat.

