You press against the right eye of the cat until it falls back into its socket and the entire body goes limp with mechanical obedience. The MANAGER gasps but your attention remains on the insides of the robotic creature, now revealed via an opening on its stomach. The mechanics are not particularly unique or advanced. Miniature pistons and a series of wires leading to the processor which, thankfully, doesn’t seem to be the issue here.

It’s not difficult to identify the problem, some bad wiring and loose connectors. You unpack the repair kit and begin your work. The MANAGER watches your hands, unable to hide the concern brimming around his dark blue irises. For a moment you feel as though you are operating on an actual living thing.

