The kitchen of Notre Feu is cramped and furiously hot. There's hardly enough room for a stove and a sink. The chef, JULIA, cracks an egg into a scorching pan of rice with such focus that she doesn't hear you come in. Once the yolk is broken, a plastic spoon mixes it into the rice.

