Pawn Shop

You walk up the steps to the front door of the pawn shop. The CLERK looks up and throws you a quick nod before buzzing you in, taking the last bite of what appears to be an egg and cheese sandwich.

Several parallels of flame lamps illuminate the shop's crowded shelves with dancing light. The air is musty and smells of old things. Every inch of the walls are covered in shelves of various mechanical INSTRUMENTS. A few articles of fine CLOTHING hang on the walls, but the dust gathering on their shoulder pads speaks to the lack of demand. A few WEAPONS lay inert beneath the glass counter. A security CAMERA in the corner of the shop sweeps silently from left to right.

“I guess I owe you some sort of thanks unless there’s another hired hand with an eyeless sick child giving away food tokens," she says as she chews.

ISAAC doesn’t seem to register that this comment is referring to him. His lenses seem to be focused in on some sort of MANUSCRIPT draped beneath a CLOWN figurine.

“Yea, anyways, thanks,” a quick grimace crosses her face before being replaced by something else.

ANIMUS: It’s not really a smile, but she’s no longer actively wishing you were dead.

“I’m Colette, by the way. We can pay you back next month if you’re still here.”

