He laughs and takes a long sip from his glass.
"I didn't," he says. "He found me. I was a gunner for the army of Curia, a border planet in the Taurus const. My home. During The Divide, Curia began trading with a nearby Geminian planet and eventually came to consider itself part of their const. Their council was fair and stable. Well, the fold engines brought everyone back together and Taurus sent representatives to assess and relcaim our mineral fields. They were sent back with bullets in their heads and a civil war broke out.

Anyways, my unit went down toward the worst of the fighting and I woke up in a field hospital. Isaac's lenses looking down at me. Into me. We spoke, or maybe I should say he spoke. It was like he knew me, had always known me. He helped me realize I was fighting the wrong war. He called me to fight for him. So I defected and fled as soon as my legs worked again. I was fourteen and I've been at his side ever since."

