Bluèl & GasTechnin Acreage Port

 Overall clad workers scatter and regroup throughout the port's expansive space, jumping over cables and fuel lines. The smell of burning of exhaust and various gasses cling immediately to your throat. You see your ship, THE VIGIL, dwarfed by enormous tankercrafts parked on either side. The spotlights of arriving and departing ships sweep the port, illuminating the scene with white light and shifting shadows.

________________________________________________________
The panels of your ship's hull are open like fish gills. Most of JULIA is hidden within. You hear loud metalic banging and the occasional sound of a drill.

As you approach, JULIA'S head and shoulders emerge from THE VIGIL shined with sweat. She tosses a wrench to the ground and walks toward you. She's somehow angrier than last you saw her.

SINEW: I'm impressed.

"What the fuck did you do to her," she shouts across the port as she closes the distance between you. "This is a fucking Corvor A-Class with a fucking unstable fold engine and you let it take a hit like this. You don't deserve her. No one in the acreage has ever deserved anything less," she takes a deep and futile calming breath and begins walking back to your ship.

"Repairs will be done in a few minutes. Only because I'm really fucking good though. Now fuck off!"

