 PRESS ANY KEY

"I have great news," he says brightly when he finally joins you on the street corner. People passing by on the sidewalk give a wide berth, like a river rushing around a stone. "Now I've spoken with our Virgo home office and you won't need to pay any of the credits for the use of our port or our fiery chef/engineer, Julia!"

ANIMUS: Do not be fooled. This is not, in fact, great news.

ISAAC speaks from your elbow:

"The coin is yours.
You can have it today."

The SECRETARY seems surprised to hear ISAAC speak, but carries on regardless.

"Uh, no, nonsense. Your money is no good here...quite literally actually. You've been blessed with the opportunity to pay the old fashioned way: hard work!"

SYNAPSE: Perhaps we should have seen this coming. Desperate planets often pull this scam on visitors. It's surprisingly effective. He'll have already locked down our ship's engine remotely. He might even have a buyer for it.

