"Oh it's a great contract," he exclaims. "I'm honestly a little jealous. You'll start right where the action is: Six miles beneath the surface of Bluèl at one of our direct extraction sites. After about 10 months on the job, you and GasTechnin should be squared. Plus training and boarding costs, of course."

"Why humor the fool whom death would love to find," ISAAC says, not bothering to lower his voice. "We leave tonight."

The SECRETARY pretends not to hear ISAAC, but his smile falters slightly.

Talk to GasTechnin Secretary  about...
