NORTHERN LANE, CIVIC RESOURCE DISTRICT

The northern end of the CR District is home to more small shops lit by the flame lamps you've become accustomed to, burning in the cold wind. The tracks of a light rail STATION cut across the district's lane. Beyond the tracks you see a long paved road that leads to the port, where you ship is waiting. You can still hear the crowd inside the bar. The windows of an OFFICE building glow with bright clean light.

There is a PROTESTER on the street corner, yelling slogans to an uncaring river of workers. A few smokers are igniting near the entrance of the BAR, huddling around one of the flame lamps.
