SINEW: Yes. yes, act now. He has this coming. I can taste the hate of this planet converging toward a hollow where his heart should be. Bitter like mustard seeds broken bewteen our teeth. Break him.

ANIMUS: August 18, 3019. It's morning and hot and humid on a planet named for a ancient movie star. A man's wife asks him again to sign the papers, to end a union that ended long ago. His daughter sits at the kitchen table pretending not to hear. He mumbles something before draining the rest of his coffee and going to work. He is late and his boss notices and his supervisor too. Last warning, Willart. He finds his place on the factory line, stamping out ammunition for a weapon he will never weild. For you. For this moment. For a dedicated secretary of GasTechnin Interconstellation Enterprises.

SINEW: Now.

PRESS ANY KEY

Your finger shifts a fraction of an inch. A sonic boom and a flash of lightening pierce reality and sends your ears ringing. The metal of the pistol's barrel fails to contain the explosion, shattering, but the bullet still finds its mark. The SECRETARY moves to clutch his chest where a bed of roses has begun to bloom, but his arms fail and collapse to his sides. His faces finds the keyboard of his terminal as he falls forward, then down to the floor.

Smoke like a lullaby drifts from the shattered barrel of your weapon.

ANIMUS: The fourteenth. Forgive us.

SINEW: We're still here. You're welcome.

SYNAPSE: Silence, both of you. Someone will have heard that shot. We need to hurry.

ISAAC stands unconcerned by the unfolded chaos.

"You met the moment with action.
Take control of the TERMINAL and set us free."

