THE VIGIL

The TERMINAL next to the pilot's seat handles most basic ship commands. The cold winds of Bluèl find their way into the cabin through your ships open door.

The instrument panel of your ship glows with lights and readouts of various colors.

DESMOND stands behind you.

You sit in the pilot's seat of The Vigil, eager to get off planet before anyone discovers the secretary's body. The instrument panel of your ship glows with lights and readouts of various colors. The lockdown is no longer keeping you here.

DESMOND falls drunkenly into a seat.

SINEW: Looks like he found a few more drink tokens.

"Did you hear that gunshot?," he says, his words slurring. "It sounded like your seven-shot, Lain."

You ignore the unsaid question and power up the ship's engines.

