The ship's door closes and locks before your ship lifts from the ground and into the sky, the city of Bluel shrinking into miniature. You look at it one last time before pulling up on the controls. Your ship suddenly falls away from the planet up into the darkness of the acreage.

PRESS ANY KEY
THE VIGIL

The Vigil hangs small and vulnerable in the blackness of the acreage.

You take a moment to double check fold engine status lines. Your terminal confirms that its primed and ready.

You look out the portside window and see Bluèl in its entirety. Beneath massive smears of gray, a single island stretches across the surface, surrounded by dark blue water. The sun is eclipsed entirely by the planet, its rays of light beaming out around it like a halo.

DESMOND shifts uncomfortably in his seat.

"Time for the fold...I hate this part," he says to no one in particular.

He pulls out his revolver and drops it into a cubby built into the ships interior. It closes automatically and a light on the door turns red.

Your ship's TERMINAL waits for your next command.
> x terminal

> x terminal

SHIP CONTROLS
1: TAKE OFF
2: ENGAGE FOLD ENGINES
3: LANDING SEQUENCES
4: EXIT MENU
> 2
An error message flashes on the terminal screen: UNSECURED WEAPONS DETECTED.

You dislodge the gun from beneath your coat and drop it into a small cubby which closes automatically. A light on the face of the door switches from green to red.

You turn back to the terminal and press "ENGAGE FOLD ENGINES" again.

This time the ship obeys and you feel the ohm of the fold engine rising beneath you feet and then throughout your bones. The pinprick stars and black of the acreage smear and dislocate before being swept away by infinite layers of pulsating rainbows.

PRESS ANY KEY

The beauty of folded space is interrupted by a sense of deep nostalgia. A universal side effect of fold space travel, but no less difficult to endure. You pull a flask of whiskey. It won't help, it never does, but you take a swig anyways.

The  feeling grows until your heart begins breaking for every person you’ve ever cared for, even briefly. You want to run through the front door of every place you’ve called home. To see your father one more time. It’s more than you can bear, but your firearm is safely locked away.

SINEW: We can endure this.

SYNAPSE: But we only know that from experience.

ANIMUS: Here, in this moment, we feel as though we will die.

PRESS ANY KEY

THE VIGIL

DESMOND shifts uneasily in his seat, his face turned resolutely toward the wall. He is so rarely silent, without a story to tell or observation to announce, but fold travel never fails to sill his tongue.

ANIMUS: He's about to cry. No, to sob. He's barely holding it back.

Together you endure the tidal waves of emotion, each crest and fall.

After twenty minutes or so, the colors begin to dissipate and the grip around your heart loosens.

PRESS ANY KEY

You look out the starboard window of your ship. The light of a nearby sun, and one a greater distance away, ignites the planet in an emerald glow.

Even from orbit, you can see the city of Surst, twinkling on the surface of the planet like a handful of diamonds.

It's been a long road, but you're finally almost done with this job.

Your ship's TERMINAL waits for your next command.
> x terminal

